name: thylakoid membrane
description: "The pigmented membrane of any thylakoid." [GOC:jl, GOC:pr]

name: plastid membrane
description: "Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a plastid and form the plastid envelope." [GOC:mah]

name: photosynthetic membrane
description: "A membrane enriched in complexes formed of reaction centers, accessory pigments and electron carriers, in which photosynthetic reactions take place." [GOC:ds, GOC:mah]

name: plastid envelope
description: "The double lipid bilayer enclosing a plastid and separating its contents from the rest of the cytoplasm; includes the intermembrane space." [GOC:jy]
